WEBVTT

00:06:29.120 --> 00:06:32.136
"Uktub," write, in the imperative.

00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:34.056
What do those things have in common?

00:06:34.080 --> 00:06:36.176
All those things have in common

00:06:36.200 --> 00:06:39.736
the consonants sitting
in the middle like pillars.

00:06:39.760 --> 00:06:41.216
They stay still,

00:06:41.240 --> 00:06:44.376
and the vowels
dance around the consonants.

00:06:44.400 --> 00:06:47.576
Who wouldn't want to roll
that around in their mouths?

00:06:47.600 --> 00:06:49.016
You can get that from Hebrew,

00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:52.696
you can get that from Ethiopia's
main language, Amharic.

00:06:52.720 --> 00:06:54.136
That's fun.

00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:57.576
Or languages have different word orders.

00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:59.816
Learning how to speak
with different word order

00:06:59.840 --> 00:07:04.816
is like driving on the different side
of a street if you go to certain country,